First, include the `chessboard` package in your LaTeX document preamble:

```latex
\documentclass[a4paper]{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}

\begin{document}
```

Next, you can define a FEN string as a LaTeX macro and use it to set up the chessboard:

```latex
\def\myFEN{rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1}
\chessboard[setfen=\myFEN]
```

In this example, `\myFEN` is a FEN string that represents the starting position of a chess game. You can replace it with the actual FEN string you have.

If you want to include the chessboard in a figure environment with a caption, you can do the following:

```latex
